#CQ: What unit is used to express the time spent in extreme temperatures above boundary for a battery item?
#Story: As an auditor, I want to verify the unit used to express the time spent in extreme temperatures above boundary for a battery item in the battery passport, so that I can ensure that reported thermal exposure data is standardized and compliant with applicable regulatory requirements.
#CQ: What lower operational voltage limit is referenced when determining whether a deep discharge event has occurred for a battery item?
#Story: As a sustainability analyst, I want to access the lower operational voltage limit reference used to determine whether a deep discharge event has occurred for a battery item, so that I can accurately interpret deep discharge event data and assess the operational health and degradation risk of the battery item.
#CQ: What battery safety assessment must follow the identification of an accident event for a battery item?
#Story: As a manufacturer, I want to identify what battery safety assessment must follow the identification of an accident event for a battery item, so that I can fulfil my post-market obligations by initiating the correct safety evaluation procedures and documenting them in the battery passport.
#CQ: What is the unique identifier of a battery item that enables a link to the battery passport?
#Story: As a supply chain manager, I want to access the unique identifier of a battery item that enables a link to the battery passport, so that I can track individual battery items across the supply chain and retrieve their associated battery passport for compliance and logistics purposes.
#CQ: Which battery passport is linked to a battery item via the battery identifier?
#Story: As a recycler, I want to identify which battery passport is linked to a battery item via the battery identifier, so that I can access the battery passport to retrieve material composition and handling instructions needed for safe and efficient end-of-life processing.
#CQ: Is the battery identifier of a battery item accessible to the public?
#Story: As a market surveillance officer, I want to verify that the battery identifier of a battery item is accessible to the public, so that I can confirm that transparency requirements are met and that any stakeholder can use the battery identifier to access the corresponding battery passport.
#CQ: Is the battery identifier provided on the battery label of a battery item?
#Story: As an auditor, I want to verify that the battery identifier is provided on the battery label of a battery item, so that I can confirm that the physical battery item meets labelling requirements, ensuring the unique identifier is physically present and accessible for scanning and traceability.
#CQ: Where is the battery identifier provided when the size or nature of the battery does not allow labelling directly on the battery item?
#Story: As an end consumer, I want to locate the battery identifier alternative provision location when the size or nature of the battery does not allow labelling directly on the battery item, so that I can still access the battery passport and verify product information even when direct labelling is not feasible.
#CQ: What is the date of putting the battery into service for a battery item?
#Story: As a sustainability analyst, I want to access the date of putting the battery into service for a battery item, so that I can accurately assess the operational age of the battery item and evaluate its remaining useful life for circularity and repurposing decisions.
#CQ: Who is permitted to access the date of putting the battery into service of a battery item?
#Story: As an economic operator, I want to verify who is permitted to access the date of putting the battery into service of a battery item, so that I can implement appropriate data access controls in the battery passport and protect sensitive operational data.
#
@prefix : <http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@base <http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton/> .

<http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton> rdf:type owl:Ontology .


:BatteryItem rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Battery Item" ;
    rdfs:comment "Represents a single physical battery item to which a DPP refers. Used in CQs that link a battery item to its battery passport (DPP) via an identifier." .

:BatteryIdentifier rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Battery Identifier" ;
    rdfs:comment "Single value data element containing the unique identifier of a battery item that enables a link to the DPP (battery passport). The identifier string is given via DataElement_Value." .

:IdentifierProvisionLocation rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :MultiValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Identifier Provision Location" ;
    rdfs:comment "Multi-value data element listing where the battery identifier is provided (e.g., BatteryLabel, Packaging, AccompanyingDocument, Online). Values are ProvisionLocationValue instances; presence of value 'BatteryLabel' answers whether the identifier is on the battery label; other values cover alternatives when labeling directly on the item is not feasible." .

:ProvisionLocationValue rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Provision Location Value" ;
    rdfs:comment "Value element carrying a controlled string for a provisioning location of the battery identifier. Example DataElement_Value values: 'BatteryLabel', 'Packaging', 'AccompanyingDocument', 'Online'." .

:AccessPermission rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :MultiValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Access Permission" ;
    rdfs:comment "Multi-value data element that specifies which audiences are permitted to access a given data element (e.g., Battery Identifier, Put Into Service Date). Each permitted audience is represented by a PermittedAudienceValue value element." .

:PermittedAudienceValue rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Permitted Audience Value" ;
    rdfs:comment "Value element carrying a controlled string naming an audience permitted to access the linked data element. Example DataElement_Value values: 'Public', 'EconomicOperator', 'MarketSurveillanceAuthority', 'ServiceProvider'." .

:PutIntoServiceDate rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Put Into Service Date" ;
    rdfs:comment "Single value data element capturing the date/time when the battery item was put into service. The actual timestamp is given via DataElement_Value with xsd:dateTimeStamp. Access control is attached via hasAccessPermission." .

:ExtremeTemperatureExposureUnit rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Extreme Temperature Exposure Unit" ;
    rdfs:comment "Single value data element indicating the unit used to express the time spent by the battery item in extreme temperatures above a boundary (e.g., 'hour', 'minute'). The unit string is given via DataElement_Value." .

:LowerOperationalVoltageLimitReference rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Lower Operational Voltage Limit Reference" ;
    rdfs:comment "Single value data element containing the lower operational voltage limit used as reference for determining deep discharge events of the battery item. The referenced limit value is given via DataElement_Value (e.g., numeric value) and, if needed, its unit may be provided by an adjacent unit data element." .

:PostAccidentRequiredSafetyAssessment rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Post-Accident Required Safety Assessment" ;
    rdfs:comment "Single value data element specifying the battery safety assessment that must follow identification of an accident event for the battery item. The assessment name/procedure is given via DataElement_Value." .

:hasBatteryIdentifier rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :BatteryItem ;
    rdfs:range :BatteryIdentifier ;
    rdfs:label "hasBatteryIdentifier" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a Battery Item to its Battery Identifier data element, whose DataElement_Value is the unique identifier enabling linkage to the DPP." .

:linksToDPP rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :BatteryIdentifier ;
    rdfs:range :DPP ;
    rdfs:label "linksToDPP" ;
    rdfs:comment "Connects a Battery Identifier data element to the DPP (battery passport) it enables access to. Used to answer which battery passport is linked to a battery item via the identifier." .

:hasAccessPermission rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :AccessPermission ;
    rdfs:label "hasAccessPermission" ;
    rdfs:comment "Attaches an Access Permission (multi-value data element) to any data element (e.g., Battery Identifier, Put Into Service Date) to specify who is permitted to access it." .

:hasProvisionLocation rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :BatteryIdentifier ;
    rdfs:range :IdentifierProvisionLocation ;
    rdfs:label "hasProvisionLocation" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a Battery Identifier data element to its Identifier Provision Location multi-value data element that lists where the identifier is provided." .

:hasPermittedAudience rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :AccessPermission ;
    rdfs:range :PermittedAudienceValue ;
    rdfs:label "hasPermittedAudience" ;
    rdfs:comment "Specialized value-link for Access Permission listing audiences (as PermittedAudienceValue) permitted to access the associated data element. Presence of a value with DataElement_Value 'Public' answers whether the identifier (or another element) is publicly accessible." .

:hasProvisionLocationValue rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :IdentifierProvisionLocation ;
    rdfs:range :ProvisionLocationValue ;
    rdfs:label "hasProvisionLocationValue" ;
    rdfs:comment "Specialized value-link for Identifier Provision Location listing locations (as ProvisionLocationValue). Presence of a value with DataElement_Value 'BatteryLabel' answers whether the identifier is provided on the battery label; other values provide alternative locations." .


:hasName rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty;
rdfs:label "hasName" .

:hascity rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty;
rdfs:label "hascity" .